ow extending to the left 2 units from the dot.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR858949.g01.svg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a 4-by-4 square grid with a dot in the center and an arrow extending from the dot 2 units to the left horizontally\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR858949.g03.svg\"></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a 4-by-4 square grid with a dot in the center and an arrow extending from the dot two-thirds units to the left horizontally\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR858949.g05.svg\"></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a 4-by-4 square grid with a dot in the center and no arrow. It is indicated that v sub center-of-mass equals 0.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR858949.g07.svg\"></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a 4-by-4 square grid with a dot in the center and an arrow extending from the dot 1 unit to the right horizontally.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR858949.g09.svg\"></span></p>"],"answer":1}]